			"formula": [
				"a(n, k) = (n+k)!/(2^k*(n-k)!*k!) (see Grosswald and Riordan). - _Ralf Stephan_, Apr 20 2004",
				"a(n, 0)=1; a(0, k)=0, k \u003e 0; a(n, k) = a(n-1, k) + (n-k+1)a(n, k-1) = a(n-1, k) + (n+k-1)a(n-1, k-1). - _Len Smiley_",
				"a(n, m) = A001497(n, n-m) = A001147(m)*binomial(n+m, 2*m) for n \u003e= m \u003e= 0, otherwise 0.",
				"G.f. for m-th column: (A001147(m)*x^m)/(1-x)^(2*m+1), m \u003e= 0, where A001147(m) = double factorials (from explicit a(n, m) form).",
				"Row polynomials y_n(x) are given by D^(n+1)(exp(t)) evaluated at t = 0, where D is the operator 1/(1-t*x)*d/dt. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 25 2011",
				"G.f.: conjecture: T(0)/(1-x), where T(k) = 1 - x*y*(k+1)/(x*y*(k+1) - (1-x)^2/T(k+1)); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Nov 13 2013",
				"Recurrence from Grosswald, p. 18, eq. (5), for the row polynomials: y_n(x) = (2*n-1)*x*y_{n-1} + y_{n-2}(x), y_{-1}(x) = 1 = y_{0} = 1, n \u003e= 1. This becomes, for n \u003e= 0, k = 0..n: a(n, k) = 0 for n \u003c k (zeros not shown in the triangle), a(n, -1) = 0, a(0, 0) = 1 = a(1, 0) and otherwise a(n, k) = (2*n-1)*a(n-1, k-1) + a(n-2, k). Compare with the above given recurrences. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, May 11 2018",
				"T(n, k) = Pochhammer(n+1,k)*binomial(n,k)/2^k = A113025(n,k)/2^k. - _Peter Luschny_, May 11 2018"
			],
